randoop.types

Class ClassOrInterfaceType

  • java.lang.Object
    • randoop.types.GeneralType
      • randoop.types.ReferenceType
        • randoop.types.ClassOrInterfaceType
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    ParameterizedType, SimpleClassOrInterfaceType

    public abstract class ClassOrInterfaceType
extends ReferenceType
    An abstract class representing Java class or interface types as defined in the JLS. (See JLS, section 4.3.)
    See Also:
    SimpleClassOrInterfaceType, ParameterizedType

      • getSuperclass

        public ClassOrInterfaceType getSuperclass()
        Description copied from class: ReferenceType
        Return the type for the superclass for this type. Returns null for types that do not have a superclass. Provides the default for reference type objects, which is the Object type. (Note that this is different behavior than in reflection classes, where null is returned because Object has no superclass.)
        Overrides:
        getSuperclass in class ReferenceType
        Returns:
        the Object class type

      • isSubtypeOf

        public boolean isSubtypeOf(GeneralType otherType)
        Test whether this type is a subtype of the given type according to transitive closure of definition of the direct supertype relation in section 4.10.2 of JLS for JavaSE 8.
        Overrides:
        isSubtypeOf in class ReferenceType
        Parameters:
        otherType - the possible supertype
        Returns:
        true if this type is a subtype of the given type, false otherwise
        See Also:

      • getInterfaces

        public abstract java.util.List<ClassOrInterfaceType> getInterfaces()
        Returns the interface types implemented or extended by this class or interface type. Preserves the order in the reflection method Class.getGenericInterfaces(). If no interfaces are implemented/extended, then returns the empty list.
        Returns:
        the list of interfaces implemented or extended by this type

      • forClass

        public static ClassOrInterfaceType forClass(java.lang.Class<?> classType)
        Translates a Class object that represents a class or interface into a ClassOrInterfaceType object. If the object has parameters, then delegates to ParameterizedType.forClass(Class). Otherwise, creates a SimpleClassOrInterfaceType object from the given object.
        Parameters:
        classType - the class type to translate
        Returns:
        the ClassOrInterfaceType object created from the given class type

      • forType

        public static ClassOrInterfaceType forType(java.lang.reflect.Type type)
        Creates a ClassOrInterfaceType object for a given java.lang.reflect.Type reference. If type is a java.lang.reflect.ParameterizedType, then calls ParameterizedType.forType(Type). Otherwise, if type is a Class object, calls forClass(Class).
        Parameters:
        type - the type reference
        Returns:
        the ClassOrInterfaceType object for the given type
